    "narrative": "The offensive core for the Austin Waves today is headlined by **Jackson Merrill** (75.27) and **Kyle Tucker** (70.65), both of whom benefit from favorable matchups against Michael McGreevy. **Jackson Merrill** is our top play, as his high-upside profile is further bolstered by a 13% platoon boost and a stolen base efficiency bonus due to the opponent\u2019s slow delivery. While **Kyle Tucker** faces a similar matchup, his consistent base projection maintains a high floor even with less dramatic situational modifiers. **Jacob Wilson** (66.11) also merits strong consideration, as his leadoff role against the middling Slade Cecconi creates a significant boost in scoring opportunities, while **Drake Baldwin** (66.08) remains a high-value play if his projected second-order placement holds.\n\nOur toughest bench decision involved **Miguel Vargas**, who narrowly missed the cut with a score of 50.11. While **Miguel Vargas** projects reasonably well, he was sidelined in favor of the higher-ceiling utility options like **Marcell Ozuna** and the primary fielders who offer better synergy with our park factor adjustments. Regarding risk, the entire lineup remains subject to \"Lineup Pending\" variance; specifically, **Gunnar Henderson** faces a tricky platoon disadvantage against Weathers that suppresses his score to 56.19. We are also closely monitoring the outcome for **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** (58.22), whose score is being suppressed by a difficult 3.34 xERA matchup against Prielipp, though his xwOBA remains high enough to justify the start. \n\nOutside of our primary starters, we are keeping a close eye on **Coby Mayo** (49.04) and **Luis Garc\u00eda Jr.** (48.14) on the bench. Both players posted respectable scores, but neither could overcome the positional depth or the defensive-first efficiency metrics currently favored by the optimizer. Should any last-minute lineup shifts occur for **Dominic Smith** or **Nasim Nunez**, these bench pieces are prepared to rotate in, though we are currently comfortable riding our primary depth to maximize our 5x5 category output.",
